  "prompt": "How much does Ne-Yo typically charge to write a song?",
  "response": "Ne-Yo, being a highly successful and respected songwriter and producer, tends to charge a premium for his services. While exact figures can vary based on the project, the complexity of the song, and the client's stature, it is reported that Ne-Yo's fees for writing a song can range from tens of thousands to hundreds of thousands of dollars. In some cases, this can include not just the songwriting fee but also royalties from the song's performance and sales. It\u2019s important to note that exact numbers are not always publicly disclosed and can vary significantly depending on various factors.",
